The paper deals with reducing training overheads in FDD massive MIMO systems, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves exploiting knowledge of channel characteristics, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of beamforming, which is a technique commonly used in wireless communication systems (cs.MM).
